                <p><strong>[CE 1.5]</strong></p>
                <p>To achieve the ultimate goals of the project in an efficient way, I was assigned with significant responsibilities to be fulfilled. The major roles that I was given were the designing and supervising role in the project. <br/>
				
				<b>My duties and responsibilities included: </b></p>
                <ul>
                  <li>To perform communication to know the scope of the project</li>
                  <li>To collect the requirements for the electrical design for the project</li>
                  <li>To perform mathematical calculations and design the working drawings, wiring diagrams, wiring connection specifications, etc. for the installation</li>
                  <li>To determine the specialized electrical equipment which would require separate electrical circuit</li>
                  <li>To define the lighting design of the electrical system</li>
                  <li>To determine the electrical distribution system in the design which would provide the details of electrical wiring</li>
                  <li>To design the determined parts within the standards of National Electric Code (NEC)</li>
                  <li>To review and finalize the design of electrical system for physical implementation</li>
                  <li>To supervise the works of the electrical installation performed by the installation team</li>
                  <li>To test the physical installation of the electrical equipment their connection etc.</li>
                </ul>
                <h2 class="sample_heading">PERSONAL ENGINEERING ACTIVITY</h2>
                <p><strong>[CE 1.6]</strong></p>
                <p>As I was leading the electrical activities, I communicated with the project engineer for the feasibility of the electrical works to be done in this project. After understanding the scope of the project and the requirements of the client, it was requiring a fully new design of electrical system and later I summarized each need by listing on MS-Word. Then, I initiated the project work by designing the electrical drawing of the project. For this, I did various mathematical calculations and designed the working drawings, wiring diagrams, wiring connection specifications, etc. for the installation of the installation crew, which are described in the sections below. (ANZSCO 233311 Task 4, 9).</p>
                <p><strong>[CE 1.7]</strong></p>
                <p>According to the requirements of the client, I moved on to define the parts of the design of electrical plan. First, I performed to determine the general needs for the design of this electrical project like 220V holder outlets to be situated throughout the building for general purpose use. Moreover, I determined the specialized electrical equipment which would require separate electrical circuit made for them only. The equipment were computers, microwave ovens, cooler machines, etc. I did this as the load requirements of these equipment based on the manufacturer’s standards required separate circuitry and specialized methods of grounding. (ANZSCO 233311 Task 2, 4).</p>
                <p><strong>[CE 1.8]</strong></p>
                <p>Then, I performed to define the lighting design of the electrical system as a part of the design process, which required a huge amount of time for developing. In this system, I determined the design and calculations of the entire required lighting fixtures along with their controls. I incorporated all the required energy-saving technologies in the lighting system as per the standard needs. Moreover, I determined the electrical distribution system in the design which would provide the details of electrical wiring of the project. In this system, I included the main switchboard to receive the source of power from the serving utility, and the entire required components like as panelboards to distribute the overall branching circuits in the project, etc. In addition, I performed the calculations for finding out the amperage load and short-circuit values which determined the entire needs of the project. (ANZSCO 233311 Task 2, 4).</p>
                <p><strong>[CE 1.9]</strong></p>
                <p>After defining each part of the design plan, I progressed on to design the determined parts within the standards of National Electric Code (NEC). Also, I added the incorporated local code standards in the design plan. For the new parts of the distribution system, I considered the standards provided by the serving utility, which dictated the methods of wiring and electrical equipment necessary for the effective distribution. After then, I compiled all the determined parts to develop the design of electrical system and the entire set of electrical plans. For this, I used the tools of AutoCAD software to create the electrical plans digitally as it was easier to review and transmit the plans with this software. On the plan, I used the appropriate symbols of electrical systems so that anyone could understand the drawing.<br/><b> The workflow which I adopted while designing in AutoCAD was: (ANZSCO 233311 Task 1, 3, 4).</b></p>
				<picture>
				  <source type="image/webp" data-srcset="<?php echo $siteUrl;?>images/EE3-1-9.webp">
				  <source type="image/jpeg" data-srcset="<?php echo $siteUrl;?>images/EE3-1-9.png">
